1
00:00:00,567 --> 00:00:05,113
(Episode 5: Back to "Parenting Diary")

2
00:00:05,653 --> 00:00:07,621
(The Original Uncles pay a visit
on Parents' Day.)

3
00:00:07,956 --> 00:00:08,975
- Hello.
- Hi.

4
00:00:08,989 --> 00:00:10,457
Yu Jun, say hello.

5
00:00:10,592 --> 00:00:11,424
Hello.
He just nodded.

6
00:00:12,361 --> 00:00:12,973
- Hello.
- Hi.

7
00:00:12,974 --> 00:00:14,541
- Come on in.
- Hello.

8
00:00:14,588 --> 00:00:15,755
You haven't taught him manners, have you?

9
00:00:15,956 --> 00:00:17,323
(Big reaction to their senior's joke)

10
00:00:17,324 --> 00:00:18,791
He just nodded.

11
00:00:18,792 --> 00:00:21,527
Your voice doesn't sound
like something kids would like.

12
00:00:22,462 --> 00:00:25,531
("god's Baby Diary" was loved
by many fans back then.)

13
00:00:25,532 --> 00:00:28,267
(Tae Woo, the entertainer)

14
00:00:28,635 --> 00:00:31,704
(Ho Young, the Mommy)

15
00:00:32,039 --> 00:00:34,040
- Hello.
- Where's Yu Jun?

16
00:00:34,041 --> 00:00:35,108
(The Original Uncles' surprise)

17
00:00:35,242 --> 00:00:37,143
Yu Jun, I got you a present.

18
00:00:37,144 --> 00:00:37,977
(Intimidated)

19
00:00:37,978 --> 00:00:39,378
Good for you, Yu Jun!

20
00:00:40,147 --> 00:00:41,614
First time seeing someone
with a beard, right?

21
00:00:41,648 --> 00:00:43,116
(Yu Jun steps back.)

22
00:00:43,117 --> 00:00:44,883
He's stepping back because of you.

23
00:00:44,884 --> 00:00:46,719
(He fails to make
a good first impression.)

24
00:00:46,820 --> 00:00:48,454
Step aside.

25
00:00:48,455 --> 00:00:49,655
(The father of three feels bitter.)

26
00:00:49,923 --> 00:00:51,023
So adorable.

27
00:00:51,024 --> 00:00:51,992
(They're strangers.)

28
00:00:51,993 --> 00:00:54,493
Oh, my. He's hiding in the cave.

29
00:00:55,228 --> 00:00:57,095
Yu Jun, look, new uncles.

30
00:00:57,397 --> 00:00:58,263
Should we go say hi?

31
00:00:58,699 --> 00:01:00,667
- He's a father of three.
- Let's say hello.

32
00:01:00,668 --> 00:01:01,868
Come here.

33
00:01:01,869 --> 00:01:03,036
(Crying)

34
00:01:04,071 --> 00:01:06,239
Some things never change,
even after all these years.

35
00:01:06,240 --> 00:01:07,641
Let's give him a try.

36
00:01:07,642 --> 00:01:08,674
He's a new uncle.

37
00:01:08,775 --> 00:01:09,675
Look at his face.

38
00:01:10,077 --> 00:01:11,144
Why don't you come here?

39
00:01:11,345 --> 00:01:12,912
- Come on.
- Good boy.

40
00:01:12,913 --> 00:01:14,047
I'll let you touch my beard.

41
00:01:14,481 --> 00:01:15,714
Look at the beard.

42
00:01:15,715 --> 00:01:16,882
How interesting.

43
00:01:16,883 --> 00:01:18,717
- So fascinating.
- What's that?

44
00:01:18,718 --> 00:01:19,652
How curious.

45
00:01:20,854 --> 00:01:21,921
So fun!

46
00:01:22,489 --> 00:01:23,556
He's touching it.

47
00:01:24,791 --> 00:01:25,858
So fun.

48
00:01:26,393 --> 00:01:27,828
(Yu Jun hides between SOOBIN's legs.)

49
00:01:27,829 --> 00:01:29,562
He's cute. So cute.

50
00:01:29,563 --> 00:01:31,997
He wants you to pick him up.

51
00:01:31,998 --> 00:01:33,566
- It was too awkward.
- Who's Mommy?

52
00:01:33,701 --> 00:01:36,168
The roles aren't specifically divided.

53
00:01:36,169 --> 00:01:38,771
But when it's nap time,
SOOBIN is his mommy.

54
00:01:38,772 --> 00:01:41,640
He's already picked him out.

55
00:01:41,809 --> 00:01:42,774
- Right.
- The baby...

56
00:01:42,775 --> 00:01:43,775
The baby makes the call.

57
00:01:43,776 --> 00:01:45,310
The baby already has someone in mind.

58
00:01:45,311 --> 00:01:47,813
He has a change of heart every day.

59
00:01:47,814 --> 00:01:48,881
(Yu Jun's favorite bed: SOOBIN)

60
00:01:49,249 --> 00:01:50,716
Yu Jun, your meal has cooled
down enough now.

61
00:01:50,917 --> 00:01:52,417
Let's sit him down and feed him.

62
00:01:52,886 --> 00:01:56,322
(It's time for Yu Jun's lunch,
made by TAEHYUN.)

63
00:01:57,491 --> 00:01:58,557
Oh, my.

64
00:01:58,558 --> 00:02:00,125
(He's ready to eat now.)

65
00:02:00,260 --> 00:02:01,894
What a nice place you have here.

66
00:02:01,895 --> 00:02:02,962
How long has it been since you debuted?

67
00:02:02,963 --> 00:02:04,030
It's been eight years now.

68
00:02:04,031 --> 00:02:05,297
That long?

69
00:02:05,298 --> 00:02:06,565
- So long!
- We debuted really young.

70
00:02:06,566 --> 00:02:07,633
Gosh.

71
00:02:07,634 --> 00:02:09,401
Did you have a hard time too?

72
00:02:09,770 --> 00:02:11,804
- At the beginning, we did.
- Right after our debut, yes.

73
00:02:11,805 --> 00:02:13,606
Is that your first question?

74
00:02:13,607 --> 00:02:15,308
I didn't know they debuted
eight years ago.

75
00:02:15,309 --> 00:02:16,876
It's been so long.

76
00:02:16,877 --> 00:02:18,511
I heard one of you was born in 1999.

77
00:02:18,512 --> 00:02:19,812
- Yes, here.
- He was.

78
00:02:19,813 --> 00:02:21,114
Same as Jae Min...

79
00:02:21,115 --> 00:02:22,448
The eldest is...

80
00:02:22,449 --> 00:02:23,649
The eldest member was born in 1999.

81
00:02:23,650 --> 00:02:25,885
So we're connected like this.

82
00:02:26,253 --> 00:02:29,054
(Jae Min is 27 now,
the same age as YEONJUN.)

83
00:02:29,756 --> 00:02:31,557
(The Original Uncles: god)

84
00:02:31,558 --> 00:02:33,392
(Jae Min: Born in 1999)

85
00:02:33,393 --> 00:02:34,727
(Around the same age: TXT)

86
00:02:34,728 --> 00:02:38,597
(Yu Jun: Born in 2024)

87
00:02:38,899 --> 00:02:41,067
So cute. How nostalgic.

88
00:02:42,436 --> 00:02:43,703
It's gone now.

89
00:02:43,704 --> 00:02:44,737
Do you want cheese?

90
00:02:45,939 --> 00:02:49,174
It's so interesting
to see them watching a baby.

91
00:02:50,377 --> 00:02:54,647
(It looks almost the same
as god watching a baby 25 years ago.)

92
00:02:54,781 --> 00:02:56,181
(Flying)

93
00:02:57,951 --> 00:02:59,018
- Open up.
- Open up.

94
00:02:59,453 --> 00:03:00,420
You don't want it?

95
00:03:00,954 --> 00:03:03,222
(Yu Jun has entered a picky eating phase.)

96
00:03:03,924 --> 00:03:05,391
No?

97
00:03:05,592 --> 00:03:07,192
You don't want it?

98
00:03:07,193 --> 00:03:08,694
It was a very brief moment.

99
00:03:08,862 --> 00:03:09,762
I know.

100
00:03:09,763 --> 00:03:11,397
(Laughing)

101
00:03:11,431 --> 00:03:12,598
They're having a hard time.

102
00:03:14,734 --> 00:03:15,701
So cute.

103
00:03:16,203 --> 00:03:17,203
What is it? Water?

104
00:03:17,305 --> 00:03:18,704
- He's super adorable.
- He really is.

105
00:03:18,705 --> 00:03:20,306
He's so pretty, isn't he?

106
00:03:20,540 --> 00:03:24,109
The camera can't fully capture
his cuteness.

107
00:03:24,110 --> 00:03:25,377
- Right.
- You're so right.

108
00:03:25,378 --> 00:03:26,678
He's even cuter in person.

109
00:03:26,880 --> 00:03:27,713
Oh, my.

110
00:03:27,714 --> 00:03:29,982
(The big mommy looks
at him so affectionately.)

111
00:03:29,983 --> 00:03:32,284
But Jae Min was super cute too.

112
00:03:32,285 --> 00:03:34,353
Right. Jae Min was really cute too.

113
00:03:34,588 --> 00:03:35,454
(Approaching)

114
00:03:35,455 --> 00:03:37,690
Oh, boy. He's looking at him
in shock as he moves.

115
00:03:38,124 --> 00:03:39,925
(Here I come, Yu Jun!)

116
00:03:41,621 --> 00:03:42,588
Oh, my.

117
00:03:42,629 --> 00:03:45,130
(Sitting)

118
00:03:45,899 --> 00:03:47,199
Do you want to eat? Nom-nom?

119
00:03:47,534 --> 00:03:48,968
(This time, Yu Jun tries
to hide behind YEONJUN.)

120
00:03:48,969 --> 00:03:50,836
(Disappointed)

121
00:03:51,004 --> 00:03:51,905
Can he say "Mommy?"

122
00:03:51,906 --> 00:03:53,305
- He can.
- Yes.

123
00:03:53,306 --> 00:03:55,607
He can say "Mommy," "water," and "bonk."

124
00:03:55,709 --> 00:03:57,810
- Like, "Bonk!"
- When Jae Min was a baby,

125
00:03:57,811 --> 00:04:00,146
his second word after "Mommy" was "piggy."

126
00:04:00,147 --> 00:04:01,180
- Pig?
- Really? Why?

127
00:04:01,181 --> 00:04:02,502
- I don't know.
- He used to call him piggy.

128
00:04:02,949 --> 00:04:04,082
Piggy.

129
00:04:04,184 --> 00:04:05,151
Did you say, "Piggy?"

130
00:04:05,152 --> 00:04:06,552
You didn't call me "Piggy," right?

131
00:04:06,553 --> 00:04:07,786
Piggy.

132
00:04:08,755 --> 00:04:09,621
Stop.

133
00:04:09,723 --> 00:04:10,990
Piggy.

134
00:04:11,758 --> 00:04:12,624
Cut it out.

135
00:04:12,692 --> 00:04:14,092
Piggy.

136
00:04:15,662 --> 00:04:17,563
- Did he learn that by himself?
- Piggy?

137
00:04:17,564 --> 00:04:19,299
Didn't he learn it from seeing
the other members?

138
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:20,966
I don't know. He called him piggy anyway.

139
00:04:21,067 --> 00:04:22,567
(It's still a mystery
why he called him piggy.)

140
00:04:23,670 --> 00:04:25,304
(The big mommy carefully approaches
Yu Jun.)

141
00:04:25,305 --> 00:04:27,039
Oh, my goodness. Yu Jun.

142
00:04:27,173 --> 00:04:28,807
He gave you such a hearty meal.

143
00:04:29,409 --> 00:04:30,676
May I sit next to you?

144
00:04:31,211 --> 00:04:32,411
Can I?

145
00:04:33,446 --> 00:04:34,679
Good boy.

146
00:04:35,015 --> 00:04:36,483
(Giggling)

147
00:04:37,284 --> 00:04:38,150
Baby Mozzarella!

148
00:04:38,318 --> 00:04:39,885
Point.

149
00:04:40,554 --> 00:04:41,387
Point?

150
00:04:42,222 --> 00:04:43,730
(The playful uncle doesn't know
when to give up.)

151
00:04:43,757 --> 00:04:44,457
Point.
(Sighing)

152
00:04:45,425 --> 00:04:46,592
He wants you to stop.

153
00:04:46,760 --> 00:04:48,461
(Stop it!)

154
00:04:48,662 --> 00:04:49,929
(Disappointed)

155
00:04:49,930 --> 00:04:51,097
Oh, my.

156
00:04:51,464 --> 00:04:52,764
Thank you.

157
00:04:53,446 --> 00:04:54,233
Good job.

158
00:04:54,601 --> 00:04:56,101
- Yu Jun.
- Did you cook?

159
00:04:56,570 --> 00:04:59,338
Yes, I did. But he's only just started
eating regular food.

160
00:04:59,339 --> 00:05:02,341
That means his poop has started
to smell different.

161
00:05:02,909 --> 00:05:05,110
He's never pooped during filming so far.

162
00:05:05,211 --> 00:05:06,444
- Really?
- Yes.

163
00:05:06,445 --> 00:05:08,213
So basically, you're not that close yet.

164
00:05:08,214 --> 00:05:09,915
Yu Jun hasn't opened his heart yet.

165
00:05:09,916 --> 00:05:11,416
He knows when and where to poop.

166
00:05:12,085 --> 00:05:14,186
Jae Min used to do his business
whenever we opened his diaper.

167
00:05:14,187 --> 00:05:15,054
I saw it.

168
00:05:15,055 --> 00:05:17,624
He peed on you
as soon as you opened his diaper.

169
00:05:17,625 --> 00:05:18,657
There we go.

170
00:05:18,658 --> 00:05:20,826
(Jae Min lies down for a diaper change.)

171
00:05:21,628 --> 00:05:24,863
(He launches a surprise right away.)

172
00:05:25,665 --> 00:05:26,965
(Take this!)

173
00:05:28,535 --> 00:05:30,129
(A vivid memory even after 25 years)

174
00:05:30,170 --> 00:05:31,270
He peed on them.

175
00:05:31,271 --> 00:05:33,539
(Yu Jun, promise not to do that to us.)

176
00:05:33,540 --> 00:05:35,541
- Let's eat together.
- Yes.

177
00:05:35,542 --> 00:05:36,408
Enjoy your meal.

178
00:05:36,409 --> 00:05:37,736
We'll take care of the baby
since we're here.

179
00:05:37,737 --> 00:05:39,146
- No, it's okay.
- We'll take care of him.

180
00:05:39,147 --> 00:05:40,212
- Really?
- Yes.

181
00:05:40,213 --> 00:05:41,280
Thank you.

182
00:05:41,281 --> 00:05:44,117
Come over here and enjoy your meal.

183
00:05:44,118 --> 00:05:45,117
I'll take care of him.

184
00:05:45,118 --> 00:05:46,252
(He moves right next to Yu Jun.)

185
00:05:46,253 --> 00:05:47,019
(What?)
Thank you.

186
00:05:47,921 --> 00:05:50,523
(Yu Jun turns his back on Tae Woo.)

187
00:05:50,924 --> 00:05:51,991
Did you just hand this to me?

188
00:05:51,992 --> 00:05:52,892
Am I scaring you?

189
00:05:52,893 --> 00:05:54,393
(Help me.)

190
00:05:54,776 --> 00:05:56,944
(I'm your hairy uncle .)

191
00:05:58,365 --> 00:05:59,598
Did you sit there just to bother him?

192
00:05:59,899 --> 00:06:01,433
(Yu Jun freezes
like there's a bug on his neck.)

193
00:06:01,701 --> 00:06:02,734
(Is he still there?)

194
00:06:02,735 --> 00:06:04,069
He doesn't cry much.

195
00:06:04,070 --> 00:06:05,671
If I were his age,

196
00:06:06,506 --> 00:06:07,940
I'd be terrified to see myself.

197
00:06:08,009 --> 00:06:08,944
Right.

198
00:06:08,945 --> 00:06:10,209
- It's a new one.
- What do you want?

199
00:06:10,343 --> 00:06:13,045
(Don't look back!)

200
00:06:14,714 --> 00:06:15,580
Hey.
(Startled)

201
00:06:16,516 --> 00:06:18,917
(Distrust, nervousness, wariness,
intimidation, confusion)

202
00:06:18,918 --> 00:06:20,285
Is it good?

203
00:06:20,286 --> 00:06:21,653
Will this give you a bellyache, Yu Jun?

204
00:06:22,455 --> 00:06:24,189
What do you mean bellyache?

205
00:06:24,357 --> 00:06:26,458
He's never met you two before.

206
00:06:26,793 --> 00:06:29,128
Look how he turned his back.

207
00:06:29,129 --> 00:06:30,796
(I just might get a bellyache.)

208
00:06:31,030 --> 00:06:32,197
(Trying an airplane.)

209
00:06:32,198 --> 00:06:33,331
(No.)

210
00:06:33,332 --> 00:06:34,299
Come on.

211
00:06:35,435 --> 00:06:36,802
He knows what he likes.

212
00:06:36,803 --> 00:06:39,238
- Do you want this?
- It's okay. We've already eaten.

213
00:06:39,606 --> 00:06:40,539
Wait?

214
00:06:40,740 --> 00:06:42,708
(Oh, my mistake.)

215
00:06:43,710 --> 00:06:44,810
That's it.

216
00:06:45,211 --> 00:06:46,344
You've come all this way.

217
00:06:46,345 --> 00:06:48,114
(The food got on his hand.)

218
00:06:48,115 --> 00:06:50,048
I should wipe your hands first.

219
00:06:50,784 --> 00:06:52,086
(Ho Young takes care of him
so attentively.)

220
00:06:52,087 --> 00:06:53,652
Is that so?

221
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:56,321
Do you want to play with this?

222
00:06:56,456 --> 00:06:57,423
That's right.

223
00:06:57,424 --> 00:06:58,957
(Ho Young talks to Yu Jun
at his eye level.)

224
00:06:59,192 --> 00:07:00,192
(Opening up his heart slowly)

225
00:07:00,193 --> 00:07:01,727
Good boy. That's it.

226
00:07:01,928 --> 00:07:04,296
(His uncles find it fascinating.)

227
00:07:04,297 --> 00:07:06,532
You need to learn everything he does.

228
00:07:06,533 --> 00:07:07,699
Do you want more?

229
00:07:07,700 --> 00:07:09,635
He got close to him so much faster...

230
00:07:09,636 --> 00:07:11,537
- than when we first met him.
- I know.

231
00:07:12,105 --> 00:07:13,705
It's cold. Do you want to open it?

232
00:07:14,140 --> 00:07:15,841
Good. That's it.

233
00:07:15,842 --> 00:07:18,343
(The big mommy hasn't changed
even after 25 years.)

234
00:07:18,445 --> 00:07:20,078
(Yu Jun is excited.)

235
00:07:20,079 --> 00:07:21,012
Look at that! So strong.

236
00:07:21,481 --> 00:07:24,850
(That's the big mommy for you!)

237
00:07:25,785 --> 00:07:27,486
(Comfortable)

238
00:07:27,487 --> 00:07:30,322
Look at you. What a clean wipe. How cute.

239
00:07:30,457 --> 00:07:31,557
- Mommy.
- Mommy.

240
00:07:32,225 --> 00:07:33,458
Mommy? Do you want to get out?

241
00:07:33,459 --> 00:07:34,560
Do you want to stand up?

242
00:07:35,261 --> 00:07:36,661
(He reads the baby's mind
and acts immediately.)

243
00:07:36,662 --> 00:07:39,364
Let's stand up. That's it.

244
00:07:39,365 --> 00:07:40,333
(How did you know that?)

245
00:07:40,334 --> 00:07:41,399
Good boy.

246
00:07:42,068 --> 00:07:44,036
(Yu Jun settles
into Ho Young's arms right away.)

247
00:07:44,037 --> 00:07:45,537
He let a completely new uncle hold him?

248
00:07:46,172 --> 00:07:47,506
Gosh.

249
00:07:47,507 --> 00:07:48,540
Where do you want to go?

250
00:07:48,541 --> 00:07:50,208
That's Ho Young's magic.

251
00:07:50,610 --> 00:07:51,643
Do you want to go there?

252
00:07:52,712 --> 00:07:54,246
Let's play with the straw.

253
00:07:55,148 --> 00:07:57,416
I bet he'll cry when Ho Young leaves.

254
00:07:57,717 --> 00:07:58,984
(I think that prediction is right.)

255
00:07:58,985 --> 00:08:00,485
When did you notice that?

256
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:01,620
I'll let you hold one.

257
00:08:01,621 --> 00:08:04,056
(Ho Young's magic is so fascinating.)

258
00:08:04,924 --> 00:08:06,057
That man looks funny, right?

259
00:08:06,860 --> 00:08:08,260
He somehow looks like Jae Min.

260
00:08:08,762 --> 00:08:11,063
- Jae Min also had big eyes.
- Right.

261
00:08:11,197 --> 00:08:13,532
Then Jae Min is older than you?

262
00:08:13,533 --> 00:08:15,067
Yes, he's the same age as you.

263
00:08:15,068 --> 00:08:16,268
He's older than everyone except you.

264
00:08:16,269 --> 00:08:18,003
- He's older.
- How old is the youngest?

265
00:08:18,004 --> 00:08:19,638
HUENINGKAI and I were born in 2002.

266
00:08:20,140 --> 00:08:21,173
You're the youngest too, right?

267
00:08:21,608 --> 00:08:22,675
Yes, I am.

268
00:08:23,343 --> 00:08:24,677
Joon is 12 years older than me.

269
00:08:25,111 --> 00:08:27,446
Really? You're 12 years apart?

270
00:08:27,647 --> 00:08:29,014
What year was your mother born?

271
00:08:29,382 --> 00:08:30,415
She was born in 1969.

272
00:08:30,717 --> 00:08:32,017
Then she's the same age as Joon.

273
00:08:32,385 --> 00:08:35,187
I've met Joon before while working.

274
00:08:35,188 --> 00:08:36,154
Really?

275
00:08:37,690 --> 00:08:39,157
(While Tae Woo talks to the members)

276
00:08:39,158 --> 00:08:41,493
Where? What do you want?

277
00:08:42,796 --> 00:08:44,063
Do you want to go back to the balloon?

278
00:08:44,064 --> 00:08:46,766
(The big mommy takes care
of Yu Jun on his own.)

279
00:08:47,009 --> 00:08:49,510
Goodness. The balloon is back with you!

280
00:08:49,535 --> 00:08:50,936
Yes!

281
00:08:51,504 --> 00:08:54,673
(The two become friends 30 minutes
after meeting.)

282
00:08:54,674 --> 00:08:56,308
The balloon is here.

283
00:08:56,843 --> 00:08:58,143
There's more.

284
00:08:58,144 --> 00:08:59,144
(Interesting)

285
00:08:59,145 --> 00:09:00,112
Here's more.

286
00:09:00,113 --> 00:09:01,220
(SOOBIN is left alone by Yu Jun.)

287
00:09:01,221 --> 00:09:03,515
Is this how parents feel when they send
their kids to kindergarten?

288
00:09:03,516 --> 00:09:04,784
Does he always smile like that?

289
00:09:04,785 --> 00:09:05,651
Tell me about it.

290
00:09:05,652 --> 00:09:07,105
(The big mommy's magic makes
everyone jealous.)

291
00:09:07,106 --> 00:09:08,020
He loves him.

292
00:09:08,621 --> 00:09:11,056
Ho Young, can you move
a little farther away?

293
00:09:12,425 --> 00:09:14,760
Yu Jun looks really comfortable.

294
00:09:15,328 --> 00:09:18,864
(He's playing without even looking
at the uncles.)

295
00:09:19,232 --> 00:09:20,299
Just enjoy your meal.

296
00:09:20,934 --> 00:09:22,268
He can handle him for two hours with ease.

297
00:09:23,002 --> 00:09:23,902
(So grateful)

298
00:09:23,903 --> 00:09:25,036
I'm so grateful.

299
00:09:25,371 --> 00:09:27,539
(Thanks to Ho Young,
the uncles can focus on their meal.)

300
00:09:27,640 --> 00:09:29,674
BEOMGYU, use your plate.
I got you this for that.

301
00:09:29,675 --> 00:09:30,709
Okay.

302
00:09:31,477 --> 00:09:33,044
(Digging in)

303
00:09:33,213 --> 00:09:36,715
(Thanks to Ho Young,
they take their time enjoying their meal.)

304
00:09:37,183 --> 00:09:38,250
Goodness.

305
00:09:38,918 --> 00:09:40,252
Bonk!

306
00:09:41,020 --> 00:09:44,756
(Yu Jun gets excited
while playing with the balloon.)

307
00:09:45,124 --> 00:09:46,357
Bonk!

308
00:09:47,961 --> 00:09:49,028
Who's there?

309
00:09:49,562 --> 00:09:50,462
Who's there?

310
00:09:50,763 --> 00:09:51,730
(Screaming)

311
00:09:52,565 --> 00:09:53,465
Who's there?

312
00:09:55,668 --> 00:09:56,668
What's this?

313
00:09:56,669 --> 00:09:59,170
(Why am I so comfortable?)

314
00:09:59,171 --> 00:10:00,071
Oh, boy.

315
00:10:00,071 --> 00:10:01,704
(Admiring)

316
00:10:01,704 --> 00:10:03,004
He's a real mom, isn't he?

317
00:10:04,804 --> 00:10:07,337
- That's how we should've done it.
- It's moving.

318
00:10:07,337 --> 00:10:08,437
It's so...

319
00:10:09,471 --> 00:10:10,504
You need to stay close to the kids.

320
00:10:10,871 --> 00:10:13,437
(Just like this.)

321
00:10:14,337 --> 00:10:16,537
Did the baby enjoy filming
"god's Baby Diary?"

322
00:10:17,037 --> 00:10:18,137
We struggled at first.

323
00:10:18,137 --> 00:10:20,037
It took time for us
to adjust to each other.

324
00:10:20,037 --> 00:10:22,204
And Jae Min was 10 months old
when we started the show.

325
00:10:22,704 --> 00:10:24,871
Right. Yu Jun is older than he was.

326
00:10:24,871 --> 00:10:26,304
He could walk when you started, right?

327
00:10:26,304 --> 00:10:28,004
- Yes.
- Right. He walked in on his own.

328
00:10:28,404 --> 00:10:29,304
Now Yu Jun can run,

329
00:10:29,304 --> 00:10:30,504
let alone walk.

330
00:10:30,504 --> 00:10:32,704
He's so energetic
that he dashes around all the time.

331
00:10:32,704 --> 00:10:35,471
At 9 or 10 months,
they can't do that, can they?

332
00:10:35,471 --> 00:10:38,071
We taught him how to walk.

333
00:10:38,071 --> 00:10:39,537
Who was in charge of cooking?

334
00:10:39,537 --> 00:10:41,104
I think Ho Young cooked for him too.

335
00:10:41,104 --> 00:10:41,937
Really?

336
00:10:42,571 --> 00:10:43,704
He must have been busy.

337
00:10:44,437 --> 00:10:47,237
- He's the real big mommy.
- Ho Young, who cooked for Jae Min?

338
00:10:47,237 --> 00:10:48,337
We all did.

339
00:10:48,671 --> 00:10:50,304
- I don't remember cooking.
- Because you didn't.

340
00:10:50,304 --> 00:10:51,737
You just didn't.

341
00:10:52,537 --> 00:10:54,471
You just made a huge mess.

342
00:10:56,537 --> 00:10:59,971
As "god's Baby Diary" became popular,

343
00:10:59,971 --> 00:11:01,604
feedback would flood in...

344
00:11:01,604 --> 00:11:04,804
online every time it aired.

345
00:11:04,804 --> 00:11:07,937
Back then, we got
about 32 percent in ratings.

346
00:11:07,937 --> 00:11:09,137
(MBC's legendary entertainment show)

347
00:11:09,137 --> 00:11:11,837
- That's insane. It really was legendary.
- It's legendary.

348
00:11:12,271 --> 00:11:15,437
A producer who came up with the idea
and produced the show.

349
00:11:15,437 --> 00:11:16,471
He called me.

350
00:11:16,971 --> 00:11:18,337
"Hey, Tae Woo. What should we do?"

351
00:11:18,337 --> 00:11:19,337
"What's wrong?" I asked.

352
00:11:19,737 --> 00:11:21,471
"The show is 56 minutes long,"

353
00:11:21,471 --> 00:11:24,037
"and it's you and Jae Min for 52 minutes."

354
00:11:24,437 --> 00:11:26,071
So I thought, "Yes! I did it."

355
00:11:26,071 --> 00:11:28,304
(He was excited to become
the star of the show.)

356
00:11:28,904 --> 00:11:30,437
I thought I'd become a star once it aired.

357
00:11:31,171 --> 00:11:31,937
Did you?

358
00:11:31,937 --> 00:11:33,137
I watched the show.

359
00:11:33,137 --> 00:11:35,237
Ho Young was holding Jae Min.

360
00:11:35,871 --> 00:11:39,837
The scene where Ho Young was feeding
Jae Min milk and dozing off...

361
00:11:39,837 --> 00:11:41,004
was only about two minutes.

362
00:11:41,637 --> 00:11:42,537
(No more words needed)

363
00:11:42,537 --> 00:11:44,704
- I know what happened.
- I know how it ends.

364
00:11:44,704 --> 00:11:45,832
There was background music too.

365
00:11:45,833 --> 00:11:47,037
I already know what happened.

366
00:11:47,837 --> 00:11:48,737
For just two minutes.

367
00:11:49,204 --> 00:11:54,537
(After 56 minutes of Tae Woo,
the scene lasted only 2 minutes.)

368
00:11:58,204 --> 00:12:02,871
(The most famous scene
from "god's Baby Diary")

369
00:12:03,471 --> 00:12:06,937
The next day, all the press covered
Ho Young and Jae Min.

370
00:12:07,137 --> 00:12:10,471
(That's how the big mommy
became everyone's big mommy.)

371
00:12:11,271 --> 00:12:12,904
We were just his wingmen.

372
00:12:14,171 --> 00:12:15,771
That was forever ago.

373
00:12:15,771 --> 00:12:18,637
But thanks to that,
you became a great father.

374
00:12:18,637 --> 00:12:19,571
It really is thanks to that.

375
00:12:19,571 --> 00:12:20,704
Right?

376
00:12:21,071 --> 00:12:23,604
(He's approaching the uncles.)

377
00:12:23,604 --> 00:12:24,537
Bonk!

378
00:12:24,537 --> 00:12:26,437
(Big reactions immediately)

379
00:12:26,704 --> 00:12:28,537
(Satisfied)

380
00:12:28,704 --> 00:12:30,737
- Bonk!
- Bonk!

381
00:12:30,737 --> 00:12:33,271
Ho Young, take him to the playground
so he can play the "bonk" game.

382
00:12:33,271 --> 00:12:34,137
What?

383
00:12:38,004 --> 00:12:40,837
You're a pretty little thing, aren't you?

384
00:12:40,837 --> 00:12:42,537
You're so good at it.

385
00:12:43,737 --> 00:12:45,004
He has a few party tricks.

386
00:12:45,004 --> 00:12:47,804
He can wink and make hearts.

387
00:12:47,804 --> 00:12:51,804
- Yu Jun, show us your wink.
- Give us a wink.

388
00:12:51,804 --> 00:12:53,437
No?

389
00:12:53,437 --> 00:12:54,737
He doesn't want to wink right now.

390
00:12:54,737 --> 00:12:57,837
- How about making a heart?
- Love you!

391
00:12:57,837 --> 00:13:01,471
- Love you!
- Love you, Yu Jun.

392
00:13:01,471 --> 00:13:02,837
He's distracted because he's so excited.

393
00:13:03,171 --> 00:13:04,004
He didn't want to wink.

394
00:13:04,004 --> 00:13:05,537
Why is that so funny?

395
00:13:06,204 --> 00:13:07,204
Bonk!

396
00:13:07,204 --> 00:13:08,437
(He's completely focused on playing.)

397
00:13:08,437 --> 00:13:11,704
Ho Young's knees must have worn out
so much over those three years.

398
00:13:12,071 --> 00:13:14,137
(Ho Young gives his all.)

399
00:13:14,604 --> 00:13:18,671
(That's what the big mommy is
supposed to do.)

400
00:13:19,104 --> 00:13:21,571
Are you okay for now?

401
00:13:21,571 --> 00:13:23,604
- How are you?
- Aren't you tired?

402
00:13:24,371 --> 00:13:25,271
Do you want us to switch?
No, leave him be.

403
00:13:27,304 --> 00:13:28,471
That's what we're here for.

404
00:13:29,737 --> 00:13:31,404
Who's that?

405
00:13:32,804 --> 00:13:35,171
- Come here.
- What is it?

406
00:13:35,171 --> 00:13:37,704
Let's try going it up as high as possible.

407
00:13:38,237 --> 00:13:42,104
(Has he finally succeeded
in bonding with Yu Jun?)

408
00:13:42,104 --> 00:13:44,204
(The highest ever)

409
00:13:45,937 --> 00:13:47,071
(I want to go back to him.)

410
00:13:47,071 --> 00:13:47,937
Just like this.
(Back to the big mommy)

411
00:13:49,004 --> 00:13:50,671
The same thing happened 25 years ago.

412
00:13:53,337 --> 00:13:55,771
Jae Min.

413
00:13:58,971 --> 00:13:59,937
Are you mad at me again?
Yes.

414
00:14:00,871 --> 00:14:04,371
(He also failed to bond with Jae Min.)

415
00:14:05,004 --> 00:14:06,904
(It reminds him of the old days.)

416
00:14:07,304 --> 00:14:09,237
Look at this.

417
00:14:09,237 --> 00:14:11,571
(They try to get the baby
to touch his beard again.)

418
00:14:11,571 --> 00:14:12,504
What's this?

419
00:14:14,304 --> 00:14:16,271
It looks so funny, doesn't it?

420
00:14:16,271 --> 00:14:19,304
Maybe it's his first time seeing
something like that.

421
00:14:19,304 --> 00:14:20,204
Mommy!

422
00:14:22,071 --> 00:14:24,904
(Disappointed)

423
00:14:28,137 --> 00:14:30,771
(He goes out with HUENINGKAI
for some fresh air.)

424
00:14:31,237 --> 00:14:35,671
Mommy.

425
00:14:35,671 --> 00:14:36,904
(Yu Jun's mom's POV.)

426
00:14:36,904 --> 00:14:37,904
Hey, it's Yu Jun.

427
00:14:39,804 --> 00:14:42,137
Did you ever bring the baby
to a music show filming?

428
00:14:42,471 --> 00:14:43,304
Music shows?

429
00:14:43,304 --> 00:14:44,837
Of course. We did.

430
00:14:44,837 --> 00:14:46,371
We took him everywhere.

431
00:14:46,704 --> 00:14:48,304
We took him to every broadcasting station.

432
00:14:48,837 --> 00:14:50,871
What I felt worst about was
that we didn't live...

433
00:14:50,871 --> 00:14:52,371
in a house as clean as this.

434
00:14:52,371 --> 00:14:53,171
Still...

435
00:14:53,704 --> 00:14:55,937
No, I believe Jae Min...

436
00:14:55,937 --> 00:14:58,137
grew up so healthy...

437
00:14:58,137 --> 00:14:59,671
because we strengthened his immune system.

438
00:14:59,671 --> 00:15:00,604
That's right.

439
00:15:01,104 --> 00:15:02,571
We toughened him up.

440
00:15:03,204 --> 00:15:04,637
I heard that as Jae Min grew,

441
00:15:04,637 --> 00:15:06,537
the house got bigger too.

442
00:15:06,537 --> 00:15:08,004
- Absolutely.
- Absolutely.

443
00:15:08,004 --> 00:15:09,537
He grew, and we grew with him.

444
00:15:09,937 --> 00:15:12,671
Jae Min was still with us
when we moved to Samseong-dong.

445
00:15:12,671 --> 00:15:14,971
- We moved to Ilsan first...
- Then we moved to Samseong-dong.

446
00:15:14,971 --> 00:15:16,704
That's right.
Then we moved to Samseong-dong.

447
00:15:16,704 --> 00:15:18,604
We even upgraded the car.

448
00:15:19,837 --> 00:15:20,737
Everything grew together.

449
00:15:20,737 --> 00:15:22,637
Technically, Jae Min bought
all of that for us.

450
00:15:22,637 --> 00:15:24,737
(Jae Min had been a good boy
since he was one year old.)

451
00:15:24,737 --> 00:15:25,971
He was a golden baby.

452
00:15:26,837 --> 00:15:27,837
He really was.

453
00:15:28,471 --> 00:15:30,604
What's been the hardest part for you?

454
00:15:30,604 --> 00:15:32,637
To be honest, getting him to nap...

455
00:15:32,637 --> 00:15:35,671
isn't really an issue because we can tire
him out by playing hard with him.

456
00:15:35,671 --> 00:15:38,137
But when it comes to food,
once he entered his picky eating phase...

457
00:15:38,471 --> 00:15:42,737
Earlier, I was watching you,
and you guys distracted him too much.

458
00:15:42,737 --> 00:15:43,571
Right.

459
00:15:43,571 --> 00:15:45,337
That's why you need to divide the roles.

460
00:15:46,404 --> 00:15:47,971
Everyone else should be
doing something else...

461
00:15:48,504 --> 00:15:50,171
while one person feeds the baby.

462
00:15:50,171 --> 00:15:51,271
One person should be in charge of feeding?

463
00:15:51,271 --> 00:15:52,491
He kept looking around during mealtime.

464
00:15:52,871 --> 00:15:53,904
(There are so many uncles!)

465
00:15:53,904 --> 00:15:55,071
Because he's so distracted.

466
00:15:55,571 --> 00:15:57,171
He knows exactly
what he's talking about as a dad.

467
00:15:57,171 --> 00:15:58,104
Of course.

468
00:15:58,804 --> 00:16:00,104
(Yu Jun is back.)

469
00:16:00,104 --> 00:16:02,171
Hello!

470
00:16:02,171 --> 00:16:03,271
Look at you, HUENINGKAI.

471
00:16:03,271 --> 00:16:04,271
I know.

472
00:16:04,271 --> 00:16:06,104
Mommy.

473
00:16:06,104 --> 00:16:07,404
(I want to play there.)

474
00:16:07,771 --> 00:16:08,971
Does he like milk?

475
00:16:08,971 --> 00:16:10,004
Yes, he does.

476
00:16:10,004 --> 00:16:12,004
- He likes drinking?
- Is that so?

477
00:16:12,004 --> 00:16:13,804
He loves drinking water.

478
00:16:13,804 --> 00:16:15,337
Then let's give him some milk.

479
00:16:15,337 --> 00:16:16,171
Okay.

480
00:16:16,437 --> 00:16:18,004
(Giving him milk)

481
00:16:18,004 --> 00:16:18,871
Is it good?

482
00:16:19,637 --> 00:16:20,671
- There he goes.
- He loves it.

483
00:16:20,671 --> 00:16:21,971
I know.

484
00:16:21,971 --> 00:16:23,437
He's hungry.

485
00:16:23,437 --> 00:16:24,804
He likes it even more than snacks.

486
00:16:25,837 --> 00:16:26,737
Is it good?

487
00:16:27,137 --> 00:16:28,104
Do you like it?

488
00:16:28,571 --> 00:16:30,804
(He charges toward the milk carton
with his lips puckered.)

489
00:16:32,571 --> 00:16:34,904
- Nice. How cute.
- So adorable.

490
00:16:35,304 --> 00:16:37,137
(Smiley)

491
00:16:37,371 --> 00:16:38,204
You're done.

492
00:16:38,204 --> 00:16:40,271
(He finishes a carton in no time.)

493
00:16:40,271 --> 00:16:41,304
(Burping)

494
00:16:41,304 --> 00:16:42,704
He's burping.

495
00:16:42,704 --> 00:16:44,637
Good. Please pat his back.

496
00:16:44,637 --> 00:16:46,804
Well done. Good job burping too.

497
00:16:48,504 --> 00:16:51,504
(The uncles and Yu Jun finish mealtime
at 1:20 p.m.)

498
00:16:52,404 --> 00:16:57,904
Guys, Tae Woo and I will do our best
to keep him calm.

499
00:16:58,637 --> 00:17:00,071
So you can go out and get some fresh air.

500
00:17:00,071 --> 00:17:01,437
- Really?
- For real?

501
00:17:02,704 --> 00:17:04,237
You seem upset.

502
00:17:04,237 --> 00:17:06,004
(You caught me.)

503
00:17:06,604 --> 00:17:09,704
You haven't discussed this at all,
have you?

504
00:17:10,104 --> 00:17:12,137
Ho Young, how about I go out with them...

505
00:17:13,504 --> 00:17:15,104
and give them life advice?

506
00:17:15,637 --> 00:17:16,671
Life advice?

507
00:17:18,071 --> 00:17:19,104
All right. Go out for a breather.

508
00:17:19,104 --> 00:17:20,171
Yu Jun, we're going out.

509
00:17:20,171 --> 00:17:21,304
That's right.

510
00:17:21,304 --> 00:17:22,904
Should we disappear one by one?

511
00:17:23,504 --> 00:17:24,704
We don't need to.

512
00:17:24,704 --> 00:17:25,704
He doesn't care.

513
00:17:25,704 --> 00:17:26,771
We should all go out together.

514
00:17:27,404 --> 00:17:29,037
That way, he'll notice we're gone.

515
00:17:29,037 --> 00:17:30,671
(Here comes Tae Woo Bear!)

516
00:17:34,071 --> 00:17:35,737
He's being chased by a bear.

517
00:17:35,737 --> 00:17:37,504
"The Revenant."

518
00:17:37,504 --> 00:17:38,537
This is hilarious.

519
00:17:38,937 --> 00:17:39,804
Let's run away from him.

520
00:17:39,804 --> 00:17:42,171
(When it's actually time to leave,
they can't bring themselves to go.)

521
00:17:43,071 --> 00:17:44,537
- Just leave.
- All right.

522
00:17:44,537 --> 00:17:45,971
We'll come back soon. Thank you.

523
00:17:45,971 --> 00:17:47,371
Thank you. Take care of him, please.

524
00:17:47,771 --> 00:17:51,437
(Thanks to god, TXT can take a break.)

525
00:17:52,871 --> 00:17:55,671
(Bye, Yu Jun.)

526
00:17:55,671 --> 00:17:56,704
Bye, Yu Jun.

527
00:17:56,704 --> 00:17:57,737
We're really leaving.

528
00:18:01,204 --> 00:18:03,104
He doesn't even care.

529
00:18:03,471 --> 00:18:04,637
Do you want to go to the playground?

530
00:18:04,637 --> 00:18:06,371
(It's TXT's break time.)

531
00:18:06,371 --> 00:18:07,359
Want to play "Cops and Robbers?"

532
00:18:08,371 --> 00:18:12,204
(The uncles go to a bakery
in the neighborhood.)

533
00:18:12,204 --> 00:18:13,671
How do they like their coffee?

534
00:18:13,671 --> 00:18:15,604
- Let's buy it later.
- Later?

535
00:18:15,604 --> 00:18:17,204
I want a Jeju tangerine drink.

536
00:18:18,637 --> 00:18:21,737
(Enjoying a rare moment of leisure)

537
00:18:22,537 --> 00:18:23,904
Yu Jun wouldn't be crying, right?

538
00:18:24,371 --> 00:18:25,871
He's probably whining.

539
00:18:28,904 --> 00:18:31,537
(No worries. Yu Jun is having fun
with Ho Young and Tae Woo.)

540
00:18:32,304 --> 00:18:33,804
(Giggling)

541
00:18:39,137 --> 00:18:39,785
What's this?

542
00:18:39,786 --> 00:18:41,037
(The big mommy opens the secret door.)

543
00:18:42,137 --> 00:18:45,037
(He plays with him,
exploring every corner of the house.)

544
00:18:46,437 --> 00:18:47,604
What's in here?

545
00:18:50,137 --> 00:18:52,037
(There's a piggy!)

546
00:18:52,337 --> 00:18:53,371
(Waiting)

547
00:18:54,237 --> 00:18:55,704
(Peek-a-boo!)

548
00:18:56,271 --> 00:18:59,471
(Playing peek-a-boo in the hallway)

549
00:19:00,504 --> 00:19:01,337
One more time.

550
00:19:03,904 --> 00:19:05,304
(Yu Jun comes out for some fresh air.)

551
00:19:05,304 --> 00:19:06,071
Who's there?

552
00:19:07,079 --> 00:19:09,479
I hear something.

553
00:19:09,504 --> 00:19:10,937
(Are the uncles having a good rest?)

554
00:19:10,937 --> 00:19:12,337
I hear something here.

555
00:19:12,337 --> 00:19:13,404
Let's play "BATTLEGROUNDS."

556
00:19:13,404 --> 00:19:18,237
(Thanks to you, we're having a good time.)

557
00:19:18,704 --> 00:19:20,104
Do you want to go down?

558
00:19:20,104 --> 00:19:20,937
Come here.

559
00:19:21,671 --> 00:19:22,737
Let's go downstairs.

560
00:19:22,737 --> 00:19:24,871
(Playing with the elevator now)

561
00:19:24,871 --> 00:19:31,071
Who's there?

562
00:19:31,071 --> 00:19:32,304
(Say hello to the camera!)

563
00:19:32,304 --> 00:19:33,304
Who is this boy?

564
00:19:34,904 --> 00:19:37,604
Oh, gosh. We're outside!

565
00:19:38,437 --> 00:19:41,004
(Time for another stroll)

566
00:19:41,004 --> 00:19:41,937
We're outside.

567
00:19:44,937 --> 00:19:45,971
What's over there?

568
00:19:45,971 --> 00:19:47,171
(Taking a tour while holding Yu Jun)

569
00:19:47,171 --> 00:19:48,371
Have you played here too?

570
00:19:49,571 --> 00:19:50,471
What is this?

571
00:19:51,771 --> 00:19:52,804
Is it a bunny?

572
00:19:53,104 --> 00:19:54,771
- Mommy.
- Mommy?

573
00:19:57,204 --> 00:20:00,171
The door opened.

574
00:20:00,171 --> 00:20:01,138
Mommy.

575
00:20:01,139 --> 00:20:02,472
Okay.

576
00:20:02,473 --> 00:20:04,174
- Mommy.
- Do you want to climb some stairs?

577
00:20:04,175 --> 00:20:05,709
(He found some stairs, Yu Jun's favorite.)

578
00:20:05,710 --> 00:20:06,643
Stairs!

579
00:20:07,979 --> 00:20:10,047
(I love stairs!)

580
00:20:10,281 --> 00:20:13,250
(A behind-the-scenes clip
from a producer's phone)

581
00:20:13,985 --> 00:20:18,522
(Climbing stairs nonstop for Yu Jun)

582
00:20:19,257 --> 00:20:23,260
(Thanks for all of that climbing.
We mean it.)

583
00:20:25,163 --> 00:20:26,864
Boo!

584
00:20:28,666 --> 00:20:30,567
Boo!

585
00:20:31,669 --> 00:20:33,303
(Giggling)

586
00:20:34,038 --> 00:20:37,741
(Having a great time
with the Original Uncles)

587
00:20:38,610 --> 00:20:41,245
(He's still like the big mommy,
even after decades.)

588
00:20:41,813 --> 00:20:43,013
Ding-dong!

589
00:20:43,014 --> 00:20:44,548
(Playing with the doorbell this time)

590
00:20:44,549 --> 00:20:48,206
(A guest has arrived.)

591
00:20:48,953 --> 00:20:50,887
Hairy grandpa, please open the door!

592
00:20:52,557 --> 00:20:53,757
No, he's not a grandpa.

593
00:20:54,859 --> 00:20:56,159
(Oh!)

594
00:20:56,161 --> 00:20:58,362
- Hello!
- Did you get some sleep?

595
00:20:58,363 --> 00:20:59,597
Say hi to the uncles!

596
00:21:00,231 --> 00:21:01,898
Did he sleep?

597
00:21:02,300 --> 00:21:03,233
Did he sleep?

598
00:21:03,968 --> 00:21:04,968
I wish.

599
00:21:05,837 --> 00:21:06,837
- Thank you.
- Thanks so much.

600
00:21:06,838 --> 00:21:08,272
- He has...
- Thank you so much.

601
00:21:08,273 --> 00:21:09,640
so much energy.

602
00:21:09,774 --> 00:21:11,141
Thanks for watching him.

603
00:21:11,476 --> 00:21:13,110
- Diaper time?
- You know it.

604
00:21:13,111 --> 00:21:15,345
- Let's check his diaper.
- Get him on the floor.

605
00:21:16,181 --> 00:21:18,082
- Do you want to sit?
- Yes.

606
00:21:18,216 --> 00:21:19,049
All right.

607
00:21:20,418 --> 00:21:23,287
(The uncles are naturally crowding
around Yu Jun.)

608
00:21:23,288 --> 00:21:24,187
Here's some coffee.

609
00:21:24,956 --> 00:21:26,590
This should energize you.

610
00:21:26,591 --> 00:21:28,258
- Thank you so much.
- Thank you.

611
00:21:28,259 --> 00:21:30,127
Thank you so much for watching him.

612
00:21:31,095 --> 00:21:32,695
Let him go now.

613
00:21:32,730 --> 00:21:34,264
(I don't want to.)

614
00:21:34,365 --> 00:21:35,733
He looks so relaxed.

615
00:21:36,701 --> 00:21:38,803
Don't you want to approach me?
Not even once?

616
00:21:39,537 --> 00:21:41,238
- Do you want to go to Uncle Tae Woo?
- Come!

617
00:21:41,506 --> 00:21:43,974
- Yes!
- Be brave.

618
00:21:44,510 --> 00:21:45,543
You have to come to him too.

619
00:21:46,211 --> 00:21:47,978
Yes, take a step forward when he does.

620
00:21:47,979 --> 00:21:48,746
Good boy!

621
00:21:48,747 --> 00:21:50,181
(Will he really go to Tae Woo this time?)

622
00:21:50,381 --> 00:21:51,749
(A sudden turn to the right)

623
00:21:52,050 --> 00:21:52,983
(This is the Tae Woo magic!)
- My gosh.
- He faked you out!

624
00:21:54,586 --> 00:21:55,986
- Let's get you a new diaper.
- It feels warm.

625
00:21:56,287 --> 00:21:57,287
That's a lot.

626
00:21:57,288 --> 00:21:59,022
How embarrassing!

627
00:21:59,023 --> 00:22:00,223
He doesn't cry after going anymore.

628
00:22:00,224 --> 00:22:01,758
How embarrassing!

629
00:22:02,694 --> 00:22:04,862
- Let's get you dry first.
- How embarrassing!

630
00:22:05,964 --> 00:22:07,332
How embarrassing!

631
00:22:07,333 --> 00:22:08,700
Are you helping me dry your bum?

632
00:22:09,234 --> 00:22:10,134
That's so nice of you.

633
00:22:10,301 --> 00:22:12,102
- You're a man!
- Good one, Yu Jun!

634
00:22:12,103 --> 00:22:13,939
They'll wipe your bum.

635
00:22:13,940 --> 00:22:14,971
I love that confidence.

636
00:22:14,972 --> 00:22:16,106
- You're a man!
- Confidence is key.

637
00:22:16,107 --> 00:22:18,308
- How embarrassing!
- He's lifting his legs for us.

638
00:22:18,309 --> 00:22:19,743
How embarrassing!

639
00:22:19,744 --> 00:22:21,511
- Good boy!
- Good boy!

640
00:22:21,512 --> 00:22:22,646
- How refreshing!
- You're so good.

641
00:22:22,647 --> 00:22:23,847
So refreshing!

642
00:22:23,848 --> 00:22:24,781
Are you happy now?

643
00:22:25,016 --> 00:22:26,116
Does it feel nice?

644
00:22:26,418 --> 00:22:28,318
- Is it a full diaper?
- Yes.

645
00:22:28,920 --> 00:22:30,387
- Are you ready for a new diaper?
- Ready?

646
00:22:30,655 --> 00:22:31,488
Are you ready?

647
00:22:31,956 --> 00:22:33,891
- Bonk!
- Let's go!

648
00:22:35,226 --> 00:22:36,927
What a good boy!

649
00:22:37,762 --> 00:22:39,429
Blow some cold air on him.

650
00:22:39,697 --> 00:22:40,630
(Blowing cold air)
(I can feel the wind.)

651
00:22:41,532 --> 00:22:42,632
There we go.

652
00:22:42,901 --> 00:22:44,802
- Let's put on your pants.
- Let's go!

653
00:22:46,704 --> 00:22:47,971
(A peaceful diaper change)

654
00:22:47,972 --> 00:22:49,906
Are you happy now that you're refreshed?

655
00:22:49,907 --> 00:22:52,142
(Yu Jun is so happy!)

656
00:22:52,143 --> 00:22:53,376
- How fun!
- This is great!

657
00:22:54,012 --> 00:22:55,379
- How fun!
- Awesome!

658
00:22:56,781 --> 00:22:57,948
Good boy!

659
00:22:57,949 --> 00:23:00,951
(Ho Young and Tae Woo were invited
to be thanked for Parents' Day,)

660
00:23:02,120 --> 00:23:03,187
(but they've taught TXT instead.)

661
00:23:03,188 --> 00:23:04,154
Are you having fun?

662
00:23:04,155 --> 00:23:05,222
Let's go!

663
00:23:07,058 --> 00:23:09,494
You're a light of hope for us.

664
00:23:09,594 --> 00:23:11,095
god is our savior.

665
00:23:16,534 --> 00:23:19,570
You learn to love bigger
through raising kids.

666
00:23:20,571 --> 00:23:24,307
A touching, yet hilarious story
about human lives...

667
00:23:25,530 --> 00:23:28,046
where they're experiencing the warm love
of a baby and a parent.

668
00:23:29,981 --> 00:23:33,758
(The three generations
of the Parenting Diary casts...)

669
00:23:33,782 --> 00:23:36,720
(had a great time together.)

670
00:23:36,721 --> 00:23:37,955
In 1, 2, 3!

671
00:23:38,489 --> 00:23:42,726
(Thank you to the god members,
the fathers of Parenting Diary!)

672
00:23:43,895 --> 00:23:47,431
Yu Jun, we're going to the zoo right now.

673
00:23:47,665 --> 00:23:50,033
Is it your first time at the zoo?

674
00:23:50,268 --> 00:23:51,268
Animals!

675
00:23:54,772 --> 00:23:58,875
(Full of animals Yu Jun has never seen!)

676
00:23:59,844 --> 00:24:03,079
(The uncles can't wait
for the zoo visit with Yu Jun.)

677
00:24:03,514 --> 00:24:04,981
- That's so...
- Can we touch them?

678
00:24:04,982 --> 00:24:05,748
That's so cool.

679
00:24:05,749 --> 00:24:06,950
They're moving a little.

680
00:24:06,951 --> 00:24:08,718
- I wonder what they have.
- Look over there!

681
00:24:09,854 --> 00:24:10,854
That's an alpaca.

682
00:24:10,989 --> 00:24:12,523
There's one here too. Look.

683
00:24:12,757 --> 00:24:13,690
Alpaca!

684
00:24:13,691 --> 00:24:15,425
- Isn't it too close to us?
- Alpaca!

685
00:24:15,626 --> 00:24:16,593
Hey, alpaca.

686
00:24:16,728 --> 00:24:17,795
Do you want some?

687
00:24:18,363 --> 00:24:19,363
Look at the alpaca.

688
00:24:19,364 --> 00:24:20,397
My gosh!

689
00:24:21,032 --> 00:24:21,999
What's this?

690
00:24:22,600 --> 00:24:24,501
It's having a feast.

691
00:24:25,403 --> 00:24:26,169
Thank you.

692
00:24:26,671 --> 00:24:27,604
Yu Jun, look at it.

693
00:24:28,473 --> 00:24:29,406
- What's this?
- Here.

694
00:24:29,540 --> 00:24:31,608
- My goodness.
- Do you want some too?

695
00:24:32,143 --> 00:24:34,111
(The alpacas are going to TAEHYUN,
who has the feed.)

696
00:24:34,679 --> 00:24:35,779
(Is he not interested?)

697
00:24:35,813 --> 00:24:38,015
- Yu Jun, do you want to feed them?
- He doesn't seem to hate them.

698
00:24:39,016 --> 00:24:40,850
No, keep going. What are you doing?

699
00:24:42,186 --> 00:24:44,220
No, it's not all for you.

700
00:24:44,221 --> 00:24:45,722
- I don't have any for you.
- That's a duck, right?

701
00:24:45,723 --> 00:24:46,656
(He's a chef here too.)

702
00:24:47,158 --> 00:24:49,025
- It won't stop following you.
- I know.

703
00:24:49,794 --> 00:24:51,795
(The alpaca is coming close again.)

704
00:24:52,230 --> 00:24:54,398
(TAEHYUN's confused groaning)

705
00:24:54,632 --> 00:24:56,066
I want to pet it.

706
00:24:56,868 --> 00:24:57,835
- Sorry.
- No.
I won't pick on you. Sorry.

707
00:24:58,670 --> 00:24:59,903
(They're taken aback by the bold alpaca.)

708
00:25:00,538 --> 00:25:01,371
Are you scared?

709
00:25:02,306 --> 00:25:03,473
You're scared!

710
00:25:03,574 --> 00:25:05,208
You're scared? Okay.

711
00:25:06,577 --> 00:25:07,410
(Laughing)

712
00:25:07,411 --> 00:25:08,578
Yu Jun seems scared.

713
00:25:09,547 --> 00:25:11,816
He's clutching tightly onto my arms.

714
00:25:12,050 --> 00:25:12,983
Are you scared?

715
00:25:13,518 --> 00:25:14,585
(Eating his cheek)

716
00:25:14,719 --> 00:25:15,418
(One more time)

717
00:25:15,787 --> 00:25:17,354
(His adorable cheeks are irresistible.)

718
00:25:17,355 --> 00:25:19,623
(I'm scared.)

719
00:25:19,791 --> 00:25:21,792
There are horses and ducks!
There are so many animals!

720
00:25:22,026 --> 00:25:23,593
- I see a horse.
- There's a robot too.

721
00:25:23,594 --> 00:25:24,996
- Is there a tiger?
- Look at the robot!

722
00:25:25,963 --> 00:25:28,398
(Hello, quack!)

723
00:25:28,633 --> 00:25:30,501
(Welcome, Yu Jun.)

724
00:25:31,402 --> 00:25:32,202
This one looks pretty.

725
00:25:32,203 --> 00:25:34,371
Yu Jun might like these.

726
00:25:34,372 --> 00:25:35,205
They're so cute.

727
00:25:35,206 --> 00:25:36,439
- They're adorable.
- Right?

728
00:25:36,440 --> 00:25:38,575
- Look at that, Yu Jun.
- My goodness.

729
00:25:38,577 --> 00:25:39,509
I don't have more.

730
00:25:39,510 --> 00:25:42,078
I see why they call goats evil.

731
00:25:42,079 --> 00:25:43,680
- With the horns.
- Yes, the horns.

732
00:25:43,681 --> 00:25:45,215
- And the eyes.
- They have pretty eyes.

733
00:25:45,216 --> 00:25:47,250
The black line looks like a barcode.

734
00:25:47,733 --> 00:25:48,719
Aren't they pretty?

735
00:25:48,720 --> 00:25:50,020
There are baby alpacas too.

736
00:25:50,721 --> 00:25:51,921
- Aren't those sheep?
- Are they?

737
00:25:51,922 --> 00:25:52,755
They are.

738
00:25:52,756 --> 00:25:53,790
Let's go there, Yu Jun.

739
00:25:53,891 --> 00:25:55,625
They're babies.

740
00:25:55,626 --> 00:25:56,559
- It's green!
- Look!

741
00:25:57,028 --> 00:25:59,897
(BLEET BY TOGETHER)

742
00:26:00,465 --> 00:26:01,297
(Are you sheep?)

743
00:26:01,298 --> 00:26:02,332
I hear them wailing.

744
00:26:02,633 --> 00:26:03,400
(Are you visitors?)

745
00:26:03,401 --> 00:26:04,968
(Yes, we are!)

746
00:26:04,969 --> 00:26:07,037
(We came with Yu Jun.)

747
00:26:07,038 --> 00:26:08,572
Look, sheep. Look, Yu Jun.

748
00:26:09,574 --> 00:26:10,641
What are you? You're not a sheep.

749
00:26:10,642 --> 00:26:11,909
We have a spy here!

750
00:26:12,143 --> 00:26:13,577
- What are you?
- Why are you here?

751
00:26:13,578 --> 00:26:14,644
Are you a donkey?

752
00:26:14,645 --> 00:26:17,114
There's a really handsome donkey there.

753
00:26:17,782 --> 00:26:19,282
How can a donkey be handsome?

754
00:26:19,951 --> 00:26:21,852
- This one?
- It's a handsome donkey.

755
00:26:22,987 --> 00:26:23,853
That sound!

756
00:26:24,722 --> 00:26:27,490
(The handsome donkey is giving them
a warm welcome.)

757
00:26:27,758 --> 00:26:29,692
(Nice to meet you all!)

758
00:26:30,061 --> 00:26:33,363
(Protecting Yu Jun's ears
from the unexpectedly loud noises)

759
00:26:34,132 --> 00:26:37,201
(The uncles are intimidated
by the extroverted donkey.)

760
00:26:37,301 --> 00:26:38,534
(I'm scared of donkeys too!)

761
00:26:38,535 --> 00:26:39,469
What?

762
00:26:39,904 --> 00:26:40,770
Should we keep going?

763
00:26:41,873 --> 00:26:43,039
Mommy!

764
00:26:45,643 --> 00:26:47,744
(Don't cry, Yu Jun.)

765
00:26:48,346 --> 00:26:50,280
(See you next time.)

766
00:26:50,281 --> 00:26:52,149
Mommy!

767
00:26:56,154 --> 00:26:57,621
Let's go on the carousel, Yu Jun.

768
00:26:58,189 --> 00:27:00,257
- We can ride this.
- This?

769
00:27:01,025 --> 00:27:04,227
(Yu Jun will surely enjoy it...)

770
00:27:05,196 --> 00:27:08,798
(like Jae Min did with the god uncles!)

771
00:27:09,867 --> 00:27:11,668
Or do you want to ride this instead?

772
00:27:11,669 --> 00:27:13,236
Is this his first carousel ride?

773
00:27:14,038 --> 00:27:15,038
Let's go!

774
00:27:15,139 --> 00:27:16,372
(Fussy)

775
00:27:16,373 --> 00:27:17,608
It'll be fun once it starts.

776
00:27:18,809 --> 00:27:21,147
Don't beg us to let you go again
after it's over.

777
00:27:21,148 --> 00:27:22,712
Mommy!

778
00:27:23,714 --> 00:27:24,547
Let's go.

779
00:27:25,116 --> 00:27:26,181
- Ready?
- Yes!

780
00:27:26,182 --> 00:27:28,318
- I'll take photos from the front.
- Okay.

781
00:27:29,187 --> 00:27:30,254
(The carousel ride has begun.)

782
00:27:30,255 --> 00:27:31,288
What's going on?

783
00:27:34,659 --> 00:27:36,727
Yu Jun, baby!

784
00:27:36,728 --> 00:27:39,830
- Yu Jun, baby!
- The first horse was the fun one.

785
00:27:40,331 --> 00:27:42,498
(Grabbing onto his collar in fear)

786
00:27:42,499 --> 00:27:43,399
Let's go!

787
00:27:45,203 --> 00:27:47,538
(Enthusiastic reactions
from the master beside him)

788
00:27:47,539 --> 00:27:50,174
(A goose by the door)

789
00:27:50,175 --> 00:27:51,441
Quack, quack!

790
00:27:51,442 --> 00:27:53,810
(An odd goose has appeared.)

791
00:27:53,811 --> 00:27:56,947
(A goat under the pear tree)

792
00:27:56,948 --> 00:27:58,749
(The uncles are doing their best
to make Yu Jun happy.)

793
00:27:58,849 --> 00:27:59,749
Mommy!

794
00:28:00,685 --> 00:28:03,654
(But Yu Jun seems sad.)

795
00:28:04,455 --> 00:28:06,756
(There's another sad person here.)

796
00:28:06,757 --> 00:28:07,957
Yu Jun, why do you seem so sad?

797
00:28:11,429 --> 00:28:13,630
(They missed a tear.)

798
00:28:13,631 --> 00:28:14,731
(Also getting sad)

799
00:28:14,732 --> 00:28:15,899
(Yu Jun's sadness is spreading.)

800
00:28:15,900 --> 00:28:16,967
Should we call it a day?

801
00:28:17,802 --> 00:28:19,035
Yu Jun looks so sad.

802
00:28:21,572 --> 00:28:23,473
(The carousel ride was
supposed to be fun.)

803
00:28:23,474 --> 00:28:24,574
High-five, Yu Jun!

804
00:28:24,575 --> 00:28:26,676
- High-five!
- High-five!

805
00:28:26,677 --> 00:28:28,244
- There we go!
- At least he's giving high-fives.

806
00:28:29,513 --> 00:28:32,482
- High-five!
- High-five!

807
00:28:33,050 --> 00:28:34,517
(A high-five in tears)

808
00:28:34,518 --> 00:28:35,718
Mommy!

809
00:28:36,287 --> 00:28:38,021
(It's a tear-filled carousel ride.)

810
00:28:38,022 --> 00:28:40,190
Mommy!

811
00:28:42,193 --> 00:28:46,763
(Was this song always so sad?)

812
00:28:49,600 --> 00:28:50,833
(Raising a kid...)

813
00:28:50,834 --> 00:28:51,734
(never gets easier.)

814
00:28:51,735 --> 00:28:52,736
Sorry, Yu Jun.
